Target Audience of Bright Future Secondary School Website
The website is designed to serve multiple groups of users, including:
1.	Students 
2.	Parents/Guardians 
3.	School Staff (Teachers and Administrators) 
4.	Prospective Students and Parents 
5.	Wider Community / General Public 

 Needs of Each Target Audience
 1. Students
Students need the website to help them manage their academic life easily:
•	Access to timetables and class schedules 
•	Homework, assignments, and study materials 
•	Exam results and academic progress 
•	School announcements and updates 
•	Information about events and extracurricular activities 

 2. Parents / Guardians
Parents use the website to stay informed and support their children:
•	Student performance reports and results 
•	School calendar (terms, exams, holidays, meetings) 
•	Fee structure and payment information 
•	Communication channels with teachers and school 
•	School rules, policies, and announcements 

 3. School Staff (Teachers & Administrators)
Staff need tools to manage and share information efficiently:
•	Upload and manage assignments and learning materials 
•	Record and track student performance 
•	Internal communication and announcements 
•	Manage timetables and schedules 
•	Access administrative resources and documents 

 4. Prospective Students and Parents
These users are interested in joining the school:
•	Admission requirements and application process 
•	Information about academic programs and subjects 
•	School facilities (classrooms, labs, sports, etc.) 
•	Fee structure and scholarships (if available) 
•	Contact details and school location 

 5. Wider Community / General Public
The general public may want to know more about the school:
•	News, events, and achievements 
•	School background, mission, and vision 
•	Community programs and involvement 
•	Contact information 




